Metro Pacific Drops Most in Two Weeks on Tollroad Sales Outlook

-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-10-18T02:24:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/metro-pacific-drops-most-in-two-weeks-on-tollroad-sales-outlook.html
Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  fell
the most in two weeks in Manila trading after its unit Metro
Pacific Tollways Corp. said it will likely miss its 7 billion
peso revenue target this year.  Metro Pacific Investments declined 2.2 percent to 3.05
pesos as of 9:53 a.m. local time, set for the sharpest loss
since Oct. 3. The benchmark Philippine Stock Exchange Index
declined 1.4 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in Manila at 
